# Execute Pipeline Rules

## Steps
1. Auth validated at API Gateway
2. Allowlist check
3. Load effective contract
4. Validate payload
5. Load effective mapping
6. Apply mapping
7. Load effective endpoint
8. Make downstream call
9. Validate response (optional)
10. Apply response mapping
11. Return final canonical response

## Invariants
- Direction must be derived once and passed consistently.
- Actuals always included when `includeActuals=true`.
- Errors must include canonical error model.
- Runtime endpoints (`/v1/execute`, `/v1/ai/execute`) are runtime-boundary only.
- Runtime auth must validate `RUNTIME_API_AUDIENCE`; do not reuse admin/vendor audiences.
- Vendor identity is derived from JWT claims only; request body cannot override caller identity.
- Any admin-triggered runtime test flow must still use a runtime-scoped token (runtime audience + scopes), not an admin token.
